Beresford County was named in honour of Viscount William Carr Beresford (1768-1854).

Beresford County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It contains Cooma and Bredbo . Part of the Murrumbidgee River forms the boundary in the north-west, and a separate part of the river forms part of the western boundary.
